The paper proposes a neural network for semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm is designed to work with data represented as manifolds, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subfields. The use of localities on the manifold and correlations between channels also suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE) or natural language processing (cs.CL) subfields.
